Pfizer Tells 900 U.K. Staff They Are ‘at Risk,’ Telegraph Says

-- B y   S i m o n   C l a r k
-- 
2011-05-08T09:53:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/pfizer-tells-900-u-k-staff-they-are-at-risk-telegraph-says.html
Pfizer Inc. (PFE) , the world’s biggest
drugmaker, has told 900 employees at a U.K. research and
development office that their jobs are “at risk,” the  Sunday
Telegraph  reported, citing a spokesman for the company.  Pfizer plans to close the site in Kent, southeast  England ,
where 2,400 people work, according to the report. The company
wants to transfer “several hundred positions to other sites,”
the paper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simon Clark in London at 
